  "instructions": [
    "Heat oil in a large Dutch oven over medium heat.",
    "Add onion and garlic and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add beef and cook until browned on all sides, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add tomato paste and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.",
    "Add flour and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.",
    "Gradually add chicken broth, whisking continuously, and bring to a boil.",
    "Reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, for 2 hours.",
    "Stir in cream cheese until melted and smooth.",
    "Season with salt and black pepper to taste.",
    "If using bay leaves, remove and discard before serving.",
    "Serve warm, garnished with chopped fresh herbs, if desired.",
    "Baste the top with a little oil to get a golden brown crust before serving."
